([ "Account":"annemairi", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of the Hunt. Covering the canvas from edge to edge in minute brushstrokes is a detailed image of two men hidden among the midnight green foliage of a forest clearing. The branches of the trees hang low, partially obscuring the view of the lower extremities and creating a chiaroscuro effect that brings attention to the pale coloring of their skin tones against the darkness of the background. Pale in contrast to his counterpart, the man on the right rests against the trunk of a tree, his back curved away from the roughness of the bark in a curve that is a mirror to the torso of his counterpart. Contrasting against the tanned complexion of the man on the left, a hand resting on the hip leaves a subtle impression on the skin that complements the intensity of the figures' eyes locked on one another. Between the two forms, the figure on the left has a hand raised to rest his index finger on the lips of the porcelain complexed man. A single ray of dappled sunlight slants from the upper left to the lower right, highlights on brown and blonde hair, respectively, creating small hotspots of light amid the otherwise dark composition. Almost imperceptible in the lower right-hand corner of the canvas is a small signature in crimson, all but illegible save for the E at the beginning. (\<[IronClaw:Props:Artist:Canvas]#229376\>)", "Assistee":"Chatters:AE:to:topsy", "CharObj":\, "Character":"Chatters:AE:em:emeraude", "Environment":"Allegory:Setting:Rinascita:Buildings:Palace:ItalianEstate:SecondFloor:Ballroom", "Flag":"", "Links":(\{ \}), "Notes":"\<*\> Topsy (Nov 15 09:47): (discarded)\\n\\n", "Priority":10, "Queue":"custom", "Rev":1.2, "RevTime":"1636987665", "Server":"ironclaw", "Theatre":"IC", "TimeClaimed":"1636987665", "TimeClosed":"1636987665", "TimeFiled":"1636936543" ])

([ "Account":"annemairi", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of the Expulsion of Lucifer. Decorating the entirety of the canvas is a series of minute brushstrokes in dark and moody tones that display the impassioned battle between Saint Michael and Lucifer. Closer to the foreground and slightly lower than his counterpart, Lucifer stands with his back turned slightly to the viewer, allowing an unfettered view of the sinuous musculature of his torso and legs. Poised in motion, his legs and buttocks are strained taut as he braces himself against his foe. Each tendon and muscle is visible beneath the olive-colored skin, utterly unclothed to lend further attention to the pale wings that seem to grow from within the shoulder blades of the form. Opposing Lucifer from the high ground is Saint Michael, his expression impassioned and intense as he locks his chocolate brown eyes on the hidden visage of the angel he battles against. His pale golden hair stands in stark contrast to the darker tresses of the other figure, illuminating the upper right-hand corner with an almost imperceptible appearance of light meticulously teased from the paint. The second form is similarly unclothed, but hidden partially from view by the body of the first as they grapple with one another's shoulders in the struggle. Fingertips impress upon the flesh, displaying the force with which they attempt to overpower the other. The background is dark and murky save for the outstretched wings of Saint Michael, pale in color like the skin of his lean and toned form. In the bottom left-hand corner of the canvas is a signature in bright russet ink, all but illegible save for the E at the beginning. (\<[IronClaw:Props:Artist:Canvas]#225687\>)", "Assistee":"Chatters:AE:to:topsy", "CharObj":\, "Character":"Chatters:AE:em:emeraude", "Environment":"Allegory:Setting:Rinascita:Buildings:Palace:ItalianEstate:SecondFloor:Ballroom", "Flag":"", "Links":(\{ \}), "Notes":"\<*\> Topsy (Nov 15 09:47): (discarded)\\n\\n", "Priority":10, "Queue":"custom", "Rev":1.2, "RevTime":"1636987662", "Server":"ironclaw", "Theatre":"IC", "TimeClaimed":"1636987662", "TimeClosed":"1636987662", "TimeFiled":"1636936720" ])

([ "Account":"ezralee", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of a wolf and a hound. Minute and careful strokes cover the entirety of this medium-sized canvas in a textured pattern that wraps around the edges of the piece. Placed centrally are two canines locked in a heated battle, the contrast between their forms and coloring striking. On the lefthand side, a dark-colored wolf of massive build crouches poised as if ready to lunge, his maw agape and stained crimson by the blood of his opponent. Facing him at an advantageous height, a pale-colored hound of silver fur leaps forward, his form frozen midair in stark contrast to the shadowy backdrop of the forested scene behind them. The silver fur of this hound's neck is stained sanguine from his wounds and yet he advances still to take on his adversary. Along the bottom lefthand side of the piece, a bright crimson signature spells out the name \\"Dalena\\" in an ornate and swirling script. (\<[IronClaw:Props:Artist:Canvas]#211571\>)", "Assistee":"Chatters:AE:to:topsy", "CharObj":\, "Character":"Chatters:AE:el:elle", "Environment":"Allegory:Setting:Rinascita:Buildings:Palace:ItalianEstate:SecondFloor:Ballroom", "Flag":"", "Links":(\{ \}), "Notes":"\<*\> Topsy (Nov 15 09:47): (discarded)\\n\\n", "Priority":10, "Queue":"custom", "Rev":1.2, "RevTime":"1636987659", "Server":"ironclaw", "Theatre":"IC", "TimeClaimed":"1636987659", "TimeClosed":"1636987659", "TimeFiled":"1636936833" ])

([ "Account":"ezralee", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of Kotys. Covering the entirety of the canvas is a lush textured array of brushstrokes, the pale colors muted and soft in tone. The image represented on the canvas displays a clearing in the woods, moonlight casting a pastel blue hue over the female figure featured prominently at the center of the foreground. Seen from behind, the figure appears frozen in revelrous dance, her dark ringlets highlighted in pale blue light as they flare out in chaotic array as though the subject of the painting was swirling through the long blades of grass surrounding her feet. Azure folds of sheer fabric have been draped over her outstretched arms, the swath of fabric dipping low beneath the curvature of her buttocks in dark contrast to the creamy hue of her skin under the blue-hued illumination of the moon overhead. The background is dark, blurry images of dancers in similar ecstatic revelry fading into the darkness of the trees that surround the clearing, the haze of the painted imagery contrasting against the precise details found in the subject at the foreground. At her feet, empty wine bottles scatter the ground amid prolific blue blossoms, a single flower falling from her outstretched hand and frozen midair. Tucked in the contours of the vignetted darkness of the left-hand corner, the name \\"Dalena\\" can just barely be seen among the brushstrokes. (\<[IronClaw:Props:Artist:Canvas]#185321\>)", "Assistee":"Chatters:AE:to:topsy", "CharObj":\, "Character":"Chatters:AE:el:elle", "Environment":"Allegory:Setting:Rinascita:Buildings:Palace:ItalianEstate:SecondFloor:Ballroom", "Flag":"", "Links":(\{ \}), "Notes":"\<*\> Topsy (Nov 15 09:47): (discarded)\\n\\n", "Priority":10, "Queue":"custom", "Rev":1.2, "RevTime":"1636987655", "Server":"ironclaw", "Theatre":"IC", "TimeClaimed":"1636987655", "TimeClosed":"1636987655", "TimeFiled":"1636936902" ])

([ "Account":"rexasb8", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of a serene forgotten castle. Wistfully yet with a unique hand this portrait was detailed of an old, long forgotten castle. The blue sky midway dominated by a burst of clouds hovering just over the centerpiece of the portrait, the castle itself. It rests at the edge of a lake which is calm and mirrors the entirety of the castle and the sky in great precision. ([ "Account":"rexasb8", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of a coastal sunset. The slim stem bows downward in a gradual tapered slope, toward a pointed mouthpiece, which has been crafted with a lipped bit for ease of balancing between the smoker's teeth, and boasts a band of raised ridges spiraling diagonally around the piece as a form of textured grip. ([ "Account":"lidiab", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! ENGRAVING ! Polgara's engraved silver maple chaise frame:\<[Ironclaw:Props:Furniture:Benches:Chaise]#19312\> -\> Created as the base of this chaise, two, elongated cheetahs reside as the framework. The feline heads, bearing grinning maws, act as knobs at the foot of the chaise, which bears a winged scarab stretching across the outer surface, all of which are supported from below by a pair of thin, pawed legs. The bodies stretch across the width of the piece, ending in a second pair of legs at their hind ends, supporting the head rest of the padded bench. Two serpentine tails of the cheetahs arch over one another at the head of the chaise, creating an opened, half vesica piscis where they overlap at the crest of the seat. A straight backrest acts as the head of the piece, depicting an inlaid series of hieroglyphic reliefs in amber willow; The right eye of Horus, determined by the stylized scroll beneath the lower lid which swoops to the left resides at the center of the backrest. ([ "Account":"lidiab", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! ENGRAVING ! Polgara's engraved silver maple bookshelf:\<[IronClaw:Props:Furniture:Storage:Bookshelf]#14882\> -\> The bookshelf's top edges on either side have been rounded into the form of thick dowels with ridged protrusions taking the shape of very fine pieces of rope, or corded yarn which has been looped onto the rounded edge in a series of reverse lark's head knots evenly spaced as if across the length of a thick dowel. Beneath the dowel, numerous pairs of threads dangle from the edge, looping over, under, and through into a woven swath of half-hitch knotwork, creating an overall pattern of loops, the pairs of threads sweeping into the carved depiction of the hollows beside them. At the center of either side a diamond of double half hitch knots, a duplicated variation of the process used in the surround, which create diagonal slopes, have been engraved centered around a double coin knot. The central knot depicts a quartet of paired strings that deviate from the whole, and have been strung together to take the form of an overlapping, convoluted rectangular shape with rounded edges; the pairs of cords weaving above and below the pairs opposite to create an interlinked sequence of dips and rises. ([ "Account":"lidiab", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! ENGRAVING ! Polgara's engraved silver maple low-back stool:\<[Ironclaw:Props:Furniture:Stools:LowBack]#13634\> -\> The chair in ancient Egypt, as in many eastern countries, was considered thesymbolof authority and prestige, as such they are typically heavily decorated with ornamental features representing the importance of the one seated. The seat of this stool is double coved in form, creating a swooped edge from side to side, and front to back, where the seat meets the rail of the chair back.The legs are those of lions, intended to transfer the symbolic power of the animal to the sitter. Not only are the feet facing forward, they are anatomically correct, with the front paws bearing dew claws and the rear legs bending appropriately at the knee and ankle.The elongated legs are joined by perimeter stretchers beneath the coved seat, which bind decorative openwork panels.The cutout panels are those of intertwined papyrus and lotus, which represents the unification of northern and southern Egypt. A low, slanted back angles slightly from the seat to meet a straight support, creating an open triangle profile along the side. The back of the chair is decorated along the topmost crest with a cartouche-bordered frieze of cobras, interrupted by the Aten disk, a circular representation of the sun, above their heads. An openwork image of the vulture goddess Nekhbet resides below; amber toned inlay wings spreading to either side, and acting as the low back's supportive crossrail. ([ "Account":"lidiab", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! ENGRAVING ! Polgara's engraved silver maple corner cabinet:\<[IronClaw:Props:Furniture:Storage:Cabinet:Corner]#21435\> -\> Comprised almost entirely of framed panels of various woven screening, each different weave is bracketed by thicker pieces of maple to create a randomized series of rectangular shapes.
